HEADWORD: Intenable
<hw>In*ten"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + <ets>tenable</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>intenable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Incapable of being held; untenable;
